			    STPJS 366</div>
  <p class="cont">the cannon and muskets in Missouri, I was unarmed. God will always protect me<span class="footRef">1</span> until my mission
  is fulfilled.<span class="footRef">2</span></p>
  <p class="std">I calculate to be one of the instruments of setting up the kingdom of Daniel<span class="footRef">3</span> by the word of the
  Lord,<span class="footRef">4</span> and I intend to lay a foundation<span class="footRef">5</span> that will revolutionize the whole world. I once offered my
  life<span class="footRef">6</span> to the Missouri mob as a sacrifice for my people, and here I am. It will not be by sword or gun
  that this kingdom will roll on: the power of truth is such that all nations will be under the necessity
  of obeying<span class="footRef">7</span> the Gospel. The prediction is that army will be against army:<span class="footRef">8</span> it may be that the Saints
  will have to beat their ploughs into swords,<span class="footRef">9</span> for it will not do for men to sit down patiently and see
  their children destroyed.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Resurrection</div>
  <p class="std">My text is on the resurrection of the dead, which you will find in the 14th chapter of John&mdash;&ldquo;In
  my Father&rsquo;s house are many mansions.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">11</span> It should be&mdash;&ldquo;In my Father&rsquo;s kingdom are many
  kingdoms,&rdquo; in order that ye may be heirs of God and joint-heirs with me.<span class="footRef">12</span> I do not believe the
  Methodist doctrine of sending honest men and noble-minded men to hell, along with the murderer<span class="footRef">13</span>
  and the adulterer.<span class="footRef">14</span> They may hurl all their hell and fiery billows<span class="footRef">15</span> upon me, for they will roll off me
  as fast as they come on. But I have an order of things<span class="footRef">16</span> to save the poor fellows at any rate, and get
  them saved; for I will send men to preach to them in prison<span class="footRef">17</span> and save them if I can.</p>
  <div class="topic">Salvation for the Dead</div>
  <p class="std">There are mansions for those who obey a celestial law,<span class="footRef">18</span> and there are other mansions for those
  who come short<span class="footRef">19</span> of the law every man in his own order.<span class="footRef">20</span> There is baptism for those to exercise
  who are alive,<span class="footRef">21</span> and baptism for the dead<span class="footRef">22</span> who die without the knowledge of the Gospel.<span class="footRef">23</span></p>
  <p class="std">I am going on in my progress for eternal life.<span class="footRef">24</span> It is not only necessary that you should be
  baptized for your dead,<span class="footRef">25</span> but you will have to go through all the ordinances for them, the same as
  you have gone through to save yourselves.<span class="footRef">26</span> There will be 144,000<span class="footRef">27</span> saviors<span class="footRef">28</span> on Mount Zion,<span class="footRef">29</span> and
  with them an innumerable host that no man can number.<span class="footRef">30</span> Oh! I beseech you to go forward,<span class="footRef">31</span> go
  forward and make your calling and your election sure;<span class="footRef">32</span> and if any man preach any other Gospel
  than that which I have preached, he shall be cursed;<span class="footRef">33</span> and some of you who now hear</p>
